File: SAA has been under Business Rescue since December. JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) has suspended all African regional flights until the end of May 2020. The airline says this is due to the "knock-on" effect of the earlier decision to suspend international flights. SAA Africa Regional Flights Suspended Until 31 May 2020 by eNCA.com on Scribd  SAA says the COVID-19 pandemic and attendant travel restrictions, resulted in substantial decline in demand for air travel. READ: Flights from high-risk COVID-19 countries isolated at OR Tambo South Africa has issued a travel ban on people from high-risk countries affected by the coronavirus. The ban has been issued to foreign nationals from Italy, Iran, South Korea, Spain, Germany, the United States of America, the United Kingdom and China.